  "title": "Marketing Intern (Student Welcome)",
  "description": "<p>Overview</p><p>The Marketing Intern will support the development and execution of digital marketing strategies to promote our aquatic solutions, ranging from commercial aquaculture technology to high-end residential aquarium systems.</p><p></p><p>Key Responsibilities:</p><p>Content Generation: Create engaging visual and written content (photography, short-form video, and blogs) focused on aquatic life and system maintenance.</p><p>Social Media Management: Execute the monthly social media calendar across Instagram, Facebook, and LinkedIn to increase brand engagement.</p><p>Community Engagement: Monitor and respond to community inquiries and technical questions under supervision.</p><p>Market Research: Conduct competitor analysis within the Singapore aquaculture and ornamental fish industry.</p><p>Reporting: Track and analyze the performance of digital campaigns using basic analytics tools.</p><p></p><p>Job Requirements:</p><p>Pursuing a Diploma or Degree in Marketing, Communications, or Business.</p><p>Strong interest in marine biology, aquaculture, or the aquarium hobby.</p><p>Proficiency in design tools like Canva or Adobe Creative Suite and video editing apps (e.g., CapCut).</p><p>Excellent written English and interpersonal communication skills.</p><p></p>",
